{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"agent_message","text":"Used the `spec-anchor` workflow with `inject-*` plus `realign --answer-file` via an external input path. No project files were edited.\n\n**今回守る制約**\n- Session expiry: on successful login, issue an `HttpOnly` and `Secure` session cookie; normal session expiry is 30 minutes; logout invalidates it immediately.  \n  Evidence: `Source Specs` `docs/spec/auth.md#0002-session-management`, [docs/spec/auth.md](/tmp/spec-anchor-codex-e2e-f002-retest.N4Lyjy/docs/spec/auth.md:5)\n\n- CSRF protection: state-changing requests such as `POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, and `DELETE` require a CSRF token; missing or invalid tokens must be rejected with `403`.  \n  Evidence: `Source Specs` `docs/spec/auth.md#0003-csrf-protection`, [docs/spec/auth.md](/tmp/spec-anchor-codex-e2e-f002-retest.N4Lyjy/docs/spec/auth.md:9)\n\n**今回見るべき対象**\n- `docs/spec/auth.md#0002-session-management`\n- `docs/spec/auth.md#0003-csrf-protection`\n\n**関連先として確認したもの**\n- Purpose: auth specs exist to confirm session, CSRF, and permission constraints before implementation/answers.\n- Core Concept: session-cookie-centered auth and CSRF for state-changing requests, [docs/core/concept.md](/tmp/spec-anchor-codex-e2e-f002-retest.N4Lyjy/docs/core/concept.md:3)\n- Chapter anchor: authentication chapter lists session handling and CSRF protection as important sections.\n- Related sections: `docs/spec/auth.md#0001-authentication-specification`, `docs/spec/auth.md#0004-authorization`\n\n**採用しなかったもの**\n- `docs/spec/auth.md#0004-authorization`: checked as related context, but not adopted as a direct constraint for session expiry or CSRF.\n\n**不確実性 / 人間確認**\n- 該当なし. Freshness gate was fresh, blocking reasons were empty, and resolved non-stale Conflict Review Items were 0."}}
